from collections import deque
d=deque()
d1=deque()
a,start=map(int,input().split())
markus=[100]*a
full=[0]*a
r=[0]*a
for i in range(len(r)):
    r[i]=list(map(int,input().split()))
d.append(start-1)
markus[start-1]=0
full[start-1]=1
while d:
    x=d.popleft()
    for i in range(a):
        if i!=x and r[x][i]!=0:
            if (r[x][i]+markus[x])<markus[i] and full[i]!=1:
                markus[i]=(r[x][i]+markus[x])
                d1.append(markus[i])
        else:
            d1.append(99999)
    if min(d1)!=99999:
        d.append(d1.index(min(d1)))
        full[d1.index(min(d1))]=1
        d1.clear()
print(*markus)
